there,' said Kurt with a broad gesture, which unpleasantly called into life the nearest wall: it leaned forward and slowly straightened up again. 'They've gone, gone,' elucidated Kurt sadly. 'But Karl is in front of us,' said Günther slowly and distinctly, and a resilient, beery wind caused them both to sway to one side: they halted, took a step backwards and again went on their way. 'I'm telling you Karl is there,' repeated Günther sulkily. And truly a man was sitting on the edge of the sidew